### 3. Hooks for Auto-Creating Organizations on User Signup

There are **two separate hook systems** that can be used:

#### A. Better-Auth core `databaseHooks` (on the `betterAuth()` config, not the plugin)

These are top-level hooks on the main `betterAuth()` configuration. The `user.create.after` hook fires after any user is created (signup, OAuth, etc.) and is the standard way to auto-create an organization for every new user.

From `/Users/marc/.bun/install/cache/better-auth@1.3.27@@@1/dist/shared/better-auth.B955zZIT.d.ts:1891-1908`:

```typescript
export const auth = betterAuth({
  plugins: [organization()],
  databaseHooks: {
    user: {
      create: {
        // Fires before user row is inserted.
        // Return false to abort. Return { data: {...} } to modify.
        before: async (user, context) => {
          // ...
        },
        // Fires after user row is inserted. This is where you auto-create an org.
        after: async (user, context) => {
          // The user object contains { id, name, email, ... }
          // Use the internal adapter to create org + member:
          const org = await context?.context?.adapter?.create({
            model: "organization",
            data: {
              id: user.id, // or generate a new ID
              name: user.name ?? user.email,
              slug: user.email.split("@")[0] + "-" + user.id.slice(0, 6),
              createdAt: new Date(),
            },
          });
          if (org) {
            await context?.context?.adapter?.create({
              model: "member",
              data: {
                organizationId: org.id,
                userId: user.id,
                role: "owner",
                createdAt: new Date(),
              },
            });
          }
        },
      },
    },
  },
});
```

Full `databaseHooks` type signature (supports `user`, `session`, `account`, `verification` -- each with `create` and `update`, each with `before` and `after`):

```typescript
databaseHooks?: {
  user?: {
    create?: {
      before?: (user: User & Record<string, unknown>, context?: GenericEndpointContext)
        => Promise<boolean | void | { data: Partial<User> & Record<string, any> }>;
      after?: (user: User & Record<string, unknown>, context?: GenericEndpointContext)
        => Promise<void>;
    };
    update?: {
      before?: (user: Partial<User> & Record<string, unknown>, context?: GenericEndpointContext)
        => Promise<boolean | void | { data: Partial<User & Record<string, any>> }>;
      after?: (user: User & Record<string, unknown>, context?: GenericEndpointContext)
        => Promise<void>;
    };
  };
  session?: { create?: { before?; after? }; update?: { before?; after? } };
  account?: { create?: { before?; after? }; update?: { before?; after? } };
  verification?: { create?: { before?; after? }; update?: { before?; after? } };
};
```

